   <right>
      <TextArea editable="false" pickOnBounds="false" prefHeight="900.0" prefWidth="900.0" stylesheets="@TataiStyle.css" text="Welcome to the Tatai help centre!Tatai is an interactive game that helps you learn and practice pronouncing Maori numbers.&#10;&#10;To get started, select a level on the home screen. If your knowledge of Maori numbers is limited, select 'Easy'! This level only contains numbers from one to ten and is great for beginners. &#10;&#10;If you're keen to challenge yourself, select 'Hard'. You'll need to be familiar with Maori numbers up to one hundred for this one.Once you've selected your level and entered your name, you'll enter the game mode. Here, a number will appear on the screen. It's your job to pronounce the number correctly in Maori! &#10;&#10;Press record when you're ready to start speaking. Be sure to speak clearly - pronounciation is key. &#10;&#10;Dont' worry, you'll get the chance to retry each question if you aren't happy with your first answer. &#10;&#10;Press 'Next' to proceed to the next question. &#10;&#10;At the end of the game, you'll receive a final score. This will be added to the leaderboard along with your name! &#10;&#10;To view all of your scores, click the 'Leaderboard' button on the home screen.&#10;&#10;Ka pai! You're all set. " wrapText="true" BorderPane.alignment="CENTER">
